<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>fly in the ointment, a • hair in the butter, a</xh5><p> <i>fly in the ointment, a—</i>some small or trifling circumstance which spoils the enjoyment of smth.: There is only one <u>fly in the ointment</u> offered by commercial propagandists; they want your money.</p><p> <i>hair in the butter, a</i>—(U.S. sl.) said of a delicate situation or sensitive issue: Never mind the details—which neither the Governor’s office nor anyone else is willing to share just yet—this is a real <u>hair in the butter</u>.</p> </entry>
